modules.text: A Happy Accident

After spending hours prepping and turning this Cherrywood bowl, it was all but finished. I placed it on the edge of a workbench for a moment and as I turned around, I knocked it to the ground. It landed on the outer lip and split immediately. Instead of discarding it, I tried to imagine how it could be salvaged. The result is what you see here.

details.description:
People nowadays tend to more rely on having take-out food because their eating habit has changed due to their busy life. However, despite the fact that a number of take-out containers have been designed, packages for take-out burger meal are not really developed so far.
  
Therefore, this package is designed to provide a more conve nient way of take-out for fast food industry as well as its  customers by designing handy carrier for take-out burger meal consisted of a burger, french-fries, and soda. 

The carrier will reduce the volume by about 50% compared to that today because I tried to simplify the design and minimize the amount of paper used with a hook for French fries, a sleeve  for a burger, and a hole for soda drink, which causes people to carry it easier, and more materials saving. It is one-handed,  convenient, practical, and compact, so your hands can be more   free by holding all in one.

PATENTED PRODUCT

details.description:
New concept of crayon packaging design_silk screen

Crayons are generally considered to be used by children, but there are also other potential users, which means crayons are no longer the preserve of particular users, children. Therefore, I tried to put a new concept of usability and beauty of crayon box which can satisfy all users with this packaging design.
The concept is derived from no existed borders among users. By choosing orange as a dominant color, it still seems lively although it becomes more simple and sophisticated to be able to target all people as potential users. Also, in order to protect its contents as a case, and help users use it more practical, you can make it fold in 2 different directions for standing crayons against triangular frame on the desk or rolling up to close it.
The basic concept of this can be applied in different purpose such as a pencil case.

owners.occupation: Rhode Island School of Design: Graduate in Industrial Design

details.name: CRAYON PACKAGING

modules.text:
SMARTER CRAYON BOX    [Silk Screened]
 
Crayons are generally placed and stored in such a box unfashionable and even inconvenient to take crayons out from. In other words, those crayon boxes only act to protect, or rather, just arrange crayons inside, but offer difficulties using crayons in users' experience. Therefore, I tried to put a new concept of beauty and usability to crayon box which can satisfy all users with its packaging.
 
I was thinking that a role of packaging is not only to protect its contents but also to offer more differentiated experience and usability to users. Therefore, this crayon packaging is designed in order to aim to protect its contents as a case, as well as to help users use it in a more practical way by expanding the role of its packaging. It provides two different functionalities by enabling it folded in 2 different directions, rolling from out to inside vertically to close it or flipping it over horizontally for standing crayons against the triangular frame on the desk. 

Also, by choosing orange as a dominant color, it still seems lively although it becomes more simple and sophisticated to be able to target all people as potential users.

details.description:
When I researched abandoned animals, I was really surprised that about 8 millions of animals are abandoned annually. It includes lost, and unwanted animals because of its owners' pregnancy, moving a house, or pets' health problems. They are all adjusted living in side of home and being taken care of by humans, so they suddenly become really vulnerable. They can be killed on roads, or if some are lucky, they can be rescued and sent to pet shelters.

However, more challenges are waiting for animals at shelters. Today, conditions of shelters are quite poor or even bad because of non-enough funds. It causes poor service, bad facilities, and small-limited space, that affect pets to get more stressed, more aggressive, and more diseases with poor hygienic environment. Also, shelters have difficulties hiring enough professionally trained workers. Because of this non-enough trained workers who understand and know animals well, animals can have more potentials to be abused, be illegally adopted for financial gains, and get more severe trauma or pains. Every single conditions of animal shelters today are all negatively affected and connected by each others, which is followed by low possibilities of new adoptions. Therefore, pets can be neglected even at shelter of euthanized.

Therefore, I was thinking about how to raise possibilities to be newly adopted. I thought, if facilities and service of shelters are enhanced by money from a new contribution way, or think even further, if shelters are changed in order to engage more people to come and see animals, opportunities of animals to be newly adopted can be absolutely increased.
So, I have come up with an idea that is expanding the role of current pet shelter to make it a new social place for pet lovers. Simply, by applying the idea of pet cafe to suffering animal shelters today, new shelter can become healthier and provide a new social place for pet lovers, which mainly aims to raise opportunities of animals new adoptions by allowing them to be more exposed to potential owners, and getting emotional bond.

details.description:
When people are asked location of their medicine chest , most people say “Somewhere in a drawer”.  Then, when unexpected accidents happen, people might be easily in panic. In this situation, it is difficult to remember where a first-aid kit (F.A.K) is, and patients may not properly get treated in time due to this issue.  This is because of the fact that most medicine chest design is not such sophisticated and even dull, which cause people to put it in somewhere in a drawer like they said. 
I designed First aid kit with red-cross shape which can prevent such circumstance mentioned above as it grabs eyes easily at once. 
In addition, as it is sophisticatedly designed, it is good for decoration. 

This is designed that each component has its respective space to fit perfectly. Therefore, it is always well-organized so that there is no time consuming to find what you need. Also, n order to keep hygiene of cotton swabs and band-aids, it has 2  lids, opened sharing one hinge, inside of kit.

details.description:
This 3 part project was for our 'Making' class in the Interior Architecture summer foundation program. The goal was for us to become familiarized with various materials and to create designs that accomodated their strengths and limitations. 

Assignment 1: Using only paper (no tape, glue etc..) create a 6''×6'' cube that illustrates the word ‘revolving'. It must support the weight of a large book. Create a set of hand drawn instructions to accompany it. 

Assignment 2: Using a minimum of 24' of 2x4x8's and one choice of  joint,  create an 18” x 18” cube that illustrates the word 'revolving'. The cube must 1) be one continuous loop that travels through the exterior and interior volume of the cube 2) use only 90 degree angle cuts  3) cannot use glue. 

Cube 3: In a 6''×6'' plaster cube, create a mold that depicts the negative space of your wooden cube design.
details.name: Revolving Cubes
